Equipped with six radial engines, a wingspan of 55 meters and a length of almost 29 meters, the Gigant Me 323 had an operating autonomy of about 1300 km and was able to carry up to 120 men or an equivalent load including heavy vehicles up to 12 tons. The maximum speed from the plane was 250 km/h. He was armed with 7 13 mm MG machine guns and two anti-aircraft guns. Guido Gay engineer graduated from Politecnico di Milano in 1964, of Piedmontese origin, Italian and Swiss nationality, is particularly known as "inventor" designer and manufacturer in various fields of technology. Passionate sailor and sailor, in the early 1970s he began studying teleguided submarine vehicles in history as a pioneer of this technique.&nbsp;
